node.text:
We’ve added two new Scoped Carbine courses at Maughan Ranch in Mattawa, WA:
Sept 17-19 & Nov 5-7, 2021
With Eastern Washington's rural & scenic topography as a backdrop, students will go from engaging targets at CQB to maximum effective range of their weapon system.  Developing full-field situational awareness and addressing the variables of physical and mental duress, shooters will understand what it takes to master the fundamentals of marksmanship in a practical, real-world environment. Limited to 10 students per class—register now to save your spot!

@maughan.ranch @aarondossphotography @leupoldoptics @oakleystandardissue @proofresearch @hornadymfg

node.title: Ready to get off the square range?

node.text: Performing a skill in isolation is one thing: now add wind, sun, dirt, uneven terrain, unknown distance, and integrate that skill through accurate, fluid motion. Mastery comes not only through isolated repetition but in consistent application faced with changing variables & environments . @michaelbjordan @withoutremorsemovie 🎥: @highendpew

I love training this time of the year...atmospherics are priceless!! 25 mph winds, hail, rain, and lightning ⛈ all in one session!!
See ya at the next Scoped Carbine Course in July!! @rdrgear

node.title: Playing the shooting version of HORSE.

node.text: After working behind the scenes on this project, and seeing first hand how much training, hard work, sweat, and grind @michaelbjordan put in to becoming John Clark, I am more than excited to see it all come to life on the big screen! Check out the new trailer and be sure not to miss it on Amazon Prime April 30th!

We ought to rename courses at Q Ranch the “Carbine Experience”—More than just a course, you and a small group of shooters will spend three full days learning the tenets of gun fighting while enjoying meals prepared by in-house celebrity Chef Jay of @aspensmainingredient at the ranch’s high-end lodge accommodations, testing your skills amongst some of New Mexico’s most scenic and rugged private acreage. Reserve your spot for the May Lowlight Recce & July Scoped  Carbine Courses now! (Link in profile) 🎥: @sureshgordon

💪🏽💥Repost from @gladiator_six
•
I Learned Some Stuff
——
Dialing in the @leupoldoptics Mark 5 Tremor 3 reticle, on my @triarcsystems 13.9” rifle during @followthroughbuck scoped carbine class in Raton NM, on some 12” steel. This was a drill Buck had us run with unknown distances that we had to quickly calculate and engage multiple targets. I learned a ton with Buck during the 3 day class. If your looking to push the limits of your weapon system in various terrain and distances this is the class for you. 
———
- Rifle: @triarcsystems 13.9
- Optic: @leupoldoptics Mark 5 Tremor 3
- Suppressor- @surefiresuppressors RC2
- Bi-Pod @magpod 
- Eye Wear: @oakleystandardissue 
- Ear Pro: @walkersgsm Razors
- Hat: @gladiatorgunz Dad hat
- Magazine Basepad: @magpod 
———
